Fitzroy County was named in honour of Governor of New South Wales Sir Charles Augustus Fitzroy .
Fitzroy County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It lies south of the Orara River , and north of the Bellinger River , and includes Coffs Harbour .
